700334f-a.title: Bronx: 221st Street (East) - White Plains Road
700334f-a.text:
East 221st Street, north side, between White Plains Road and Barnes
Ave., showing the Hustace Farm House (also called Husted Farm House.
See Jenkins History of the Bronx). It is one of the oldest landmarks of
the region and stood on what was formerly Seventh Ave., between Third and
Fourth Streets in the village of Olinville, town of Westchester, West-
chester County. The G.W. Bromley map of 1913 shows the house no longer
to be there and the 1927 map shows its site occupied by two 2-story brick
houses, in the very center of the block on lots 26 and 29.
1906.
Gift of Randall Comfort.
